1
00:00:00,120 --> 00:00:00,920
Where’s the bathroom?

2
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:02,040
- It’s…
- Over there.

3
00:00:02,720 --> 00:00:03,280
Baby.

4
00:00:03,760 --> 00:00:04,440
How’d you know that?

5
00:00:05,920 --> 00:00:09,520
You and U somehow feel very similar.

6
00:00:10,360 --> 00:00:11,160
How so?

7
00:00:11,360 --> 00:00:14,200
U looks at North the way you look at me.

8
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:17,880
It’s like I finally have a family today.

9
00:00:18,320 --> 00:00:19,080
I love you, North.

10
00:00:19,360 --> 00:00:20,560
I love you, too, U.

11
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:25,280
NO SALTED ROLLS BECAUSE WE
DON’T KNOW HOW TO MAKE THEM.

12
00:00:26,360 --> 00:00:27,720
Try this.

13
00:00:29,320 --> 00:00:30,480
Happy to.

14
00:00:31,520 --> 00:00:33,440
- So good.
- Smells amazing.

15
00:00:34,240 --> 00:00:37,480
Can I take a few boxes home?

16
00:00:38,480 --> 00:00:39,520
It’s for my family.

17
00:00:39,520 --> 00:00:41,360
A few boxes?

18
00:00:41,720 --> 00:00:44,720
Do you plan to spike up
your Grandpa’s blood sugar?

19
00:00:45,160 --> 00:00:46,480
It’s not for Grandpa.

20
00:00:46,920 --> 00:00:49,360
It’s for my boyfriend’s mother.

21
00:00:50,440 --> 00:00:52,640
Oh, my. Oh, my.

22
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:54,560
Love is in the air and it stinks!

23
00:00:54,960 --> 00:00:55,600
Alright.

24
00:00:55,920 --> 00:00:57,000
Take whatever you want.

25
00:00:57,200 --> 00:01:00,360
But ask her to vote which of these
we should put on the menu.

26
00:01:02,280 --> 00:01:04,280
I’ll just grab a few…

27
00:01:05,280 --> 00:01:06,000
All of this.

28
00:01:06,840 --> 00:01:07,360
See you.

29
00:01:07,360 --> 00:01:07,800
Bye.

30
00:01:08,720 --> 00:01:09,520
Bye.

31
00:01:09,960 --> 00:01:10,880
Thank you for this.

32
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:24,320
The house is quite spacious,
just like how you requested.

33
00:01:24,640 --> 00:01:25,960
I am relieved you like it.

34
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:28,160
We can…

35
00:01:28,920 --> 00:01:32,240
Excuse me, did you have an appointment
to see the property?

36
00:01:32,520 --> 00:01:34,920
I’m only available to be here
for the next 20 minutes.

37
00:01:36,960 --> 00:01:37,280
Oh?

38
00:01:38,720 --> 00:01:41,360
Why did Mom suddenly
want to sell this house?

39
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:43,760
That would be too bad.

40
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:45,240
Maybe I should buy it.

41
00:01:46,240 --> 00:01:47,160
It’s full of memories.

42
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:48,760
I’m not sure what you mean, sir.

43
00:01:48,760 --> 00:01:51,120
The owner of this house is a foreigner

44
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:52,840
who has returned to Denmark.

45
00:01:54,880 --> 00:01:57,080
I think there’s been a misunderstanding.

46
00:01:57,080 --> 00:01:58,000
Hold on.

47
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:03,280
Ma’am, sir, excuse me for a minute.

48
00:02:04,360 --> 00:02:05,240
Look.

49
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:09,200
I don’t think this house belongs
to your partner’s family.

50
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:15,760
This house… it’s often rented out
to con artists to scam people.

51
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:17,160
That’s not true.

52
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:19,480
The house is full of my boyfriend’s stuff.

53
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:34,280
ISSARA PREECHAJIT

54
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:40,880
They haven’t taken anything much
from you, I hope?

55
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:50,280
Oh!

56
00:02:50,480 --> 00:02:51,240
Hey!

57
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:52,280
Hey!

58
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:08,120
Oh, you’re all here.

59
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:08,680
Did something happe—

60
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:09,800
I know the truth!

61
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:13,000
North.

62
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:14,680
What are you talking about?

63
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:16,160
I went to that house today.

64
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:18,160
The real estate agent told me everything.

65
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:21,920
North.

66
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:23,960
I— I can explain.

67
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:24,680
Go on.

68
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:27,000
I can’t wait to hear
what the hell all this was about.

69
00:04:27,560 --> 00:04:27,760
Well?

70
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:30,160
WOMAN SCAMMED BY
HANDSOME CON MAN

71
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,280
You’re going to jail.

72
00:04:39,960 --> 00:04:40,400
Nana.

73
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:41,040
Yes?

74
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:41,640
Call the police.

75
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:44,800
Nana, hold on.

76
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:47,400
If this makes headlines,
things could blow up in our faces.

77
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:48,400
I don’t care.

78
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:50,200
I’m making sure he’s going to prison.

79
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:51,840
You need to get a divorce right away.

80
00:04:52,080 --> 00:04:52,600
Right now.

81
00:04:53,080 --> 00:04:55,240
But it is past district offices’ working hours.

82
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:56,680
Go and wait outside their building!

83
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:57,400
No.

84
00:04:58,360 --> 00:04:58,960
I don’t want a divorce.

85
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:00,000
I love North.

86
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:02,600
North, you have to believe me.

87
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:03,760
I really do love you.

88
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:04,640
I’m not lying.

89
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:07,160
Who’d be stupid enough to believe you?

90
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:08,240
You have the audacity to say that now?

91
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:09,080
Pai!

92
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:09,720
Sir, no!

93
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:10,240
Pai!

94
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:11,040
Pai, calm down!

95
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:13,320
- Sir, please let go!
- Calm down!

96
00:05:13,320 --> 00:05:15,320
- Please let go.
- Pai, stop this.

97
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:16,840
Calm down!

98
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:19,320
Now call the police.

99
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:23,840
But if we do and your family finds out,
you will be in trouble, sir.

100
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,440
Can we pay the press to keep quiet?

101
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:27,640
I’ll check.

102
00:05:28,440 --> 00:05:31,600
Pai, you know…

103
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:33,600
We won’t be able to press any charges
without evidence anyway.

104
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:36,760
The only way to hold him accountable
is to sue him.

105
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:37,400
Nana.

106
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:38,120
Yes?

107
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:39,400
Get me an attorney.

108
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:41,120
I don’t want anyone my family knows.

109
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:42,040
Yes, sir.

110
00:05:42,160 --> 00:05:47,040
But this will take a while since
your family knows all the best lawyers.

111
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:47,680
North.

112
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:50,240
Gather evidence.

113
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:53,000
Yes, Pai.

114
00:05:53,760 --> 00:05:55,240
I don’t know if
I’ll be able to find any, though.

115
00:05:55,520 --> 00:05:55,960
North.

116
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:57,320
Please let me explain.

117
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:58,640
Keep your excuses for the court.

118
00:05:59,160 --> 00:05:59,880
Pai.

119
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:01,520
Let’s call it a day.

120
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:02,400
I’m tired.

121
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:03,720
Please. I just want to be alone.

122
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:05,000
But what will we do with him?

123
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:07,400
Tied him up here until the police get here?

124
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:08,960
Can we at least have him locked up
at the police precinct?

125
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:11,360
I’m not going anywhere, Mr. Pai.

126
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:13,000
I’m staying right here with North

127
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:14,200
until we’re through with this.

128
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:15,200
What right do you have to do that?

129
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:17,600
I do, though, legally, too.

130
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:20,440
Legally speaking,

131
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:24,760
the ones who are trespassing are us, sir.

132
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:25,680
Damn it!

133
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:27,400
The thief is sitting right in front of us
but we can’t do anything?

134
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:31,160
What do I have to do
for you to listen to me?

135
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:34,000
There’s nothing you can do
for me to give you a second chance.

136
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:36,680
Can I talk to North alone?

137
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:38,360
How can I be sure you won’t hurt him?

138
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:39,320
I would never hurt North—

139
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:40,040
I don’t believe you!

140
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:40,960
Stop it, all of you!

141
00:06:41,960 --> 00:06:42,720
Get out of here.

142
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:44,880
Let me talk to him alone.

143
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:45,960
Pai.

144
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,120
This is a sensitive matter.

145
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:51,360
I think we should
give North some room to think.

146
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:53,600
What if he runs away or hurts North?

147
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:56,960
How about this?

148
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:04,600
There’s a camera in this teddy.

149
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:10,360
Please forgive me.

150
00:07:11,440 --> 00:07:12,160
Excuse me.

151
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:13,400
I found it!

152
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:16,400
Face scan, please.

153
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:21,520
I’ve downloaded a tracking app
on this phone, sir.

154
00:07:21,520 --> 00:07:23,720
We will be notified wherever he goes.

155
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:26,840
Can you let me talk to North now?

156
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:30,120
Don’t cave in, North.

157
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:32,000
Yes, Pai.

158
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:42,960
At least this is better than U getting away.

159
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:47,960
I must come across like such a fool to you.

160
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:51,960
I admit I used to be a con artist.

161
00:07:52,520 --> 00:07:53,920
But I quit, North.

162
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:57,400
Because of you, I realized
I don’t want to do that anymore.

163
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:02,280
I’m serious.

164
00:08:26,880 --> 00:08:27,560
Come on.

165
00:08:29,080 --> 00:08:30,480
I don’t think I can trust you anymore.

166
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:32,720
Go away.

167
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,120
I’d rather we stay out of
each other’s way from now on.

168
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:38,120
I’m not going.

169
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:41,160
I’ll do whatever it takes
for you to believe me.

170
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:46,800
Go on and slap me if you’re so mad at me,

171
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:50,400
but I’m not going anywhere.

172
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:01,880
You slapped me!

173
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:03,560
Well, you told me to!

174
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:06,280
Oh, was that a lie as well?

175
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:07,720
How can I even trust you again?

176
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:08,520
Sit down.

177
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:09,400
Sit back down!

178
00:09:10,680 --> 00:09:11,360
North.

179
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:13,760
I wasn’t lying—

180
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,040
Stay put!

181
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:17,320
Hold on, North.

182
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:19,080
I thought you were letting me go?

183
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:33,480
Crap!

184
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:34,520
Crap!

185
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:44,720
You’re finally awake.

186
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:46,120
I’m going to have breakfast.

187
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:47,120
Oh?

188
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:48,200
What about me?

189
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:54,600
I can’t let you run away,
but then I can’t trust you if you stay.

190
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:57,160
What a headache!

191
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:59,840
Should I just take you to an animal hospital
and get you a microchip?

192
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:03,280
What vet would agree to do that?

193
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:06,000
How about this?

194
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:12,400
If you’re so afraid I’d run,
take me with you everywhere.

195
00:10:12,680 --> 00:10:13,560
I’m okay with that.

196
00:10:15,680 --> 00:10:16,280
Alright?

197
00:10:28,720 --> 00:10:29,920
Stay where I can see you.

198
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:32,000
Don’t talk to me.

199
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:32,920
Don’t bother me.

200
00:10:41,760 --> 00:10:42,160
Yes.

201
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:49,960
I’m going to sue the hell out of him.

202
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:52,560
I’ll make sure he has no place
in the world after this.

203
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,440
Good morning, Mr. Pai, Mr. Tim.

204
00:11:00,760 --> 00:11:01,400
How was it?

205
00:11:01,880 --> 00:11:03,120
Is everything okay?

206
00:11:03,640 --> 00:11:05,080
Do we still have eye on U?

207
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:07,000
Mr. U shows no sign of running away, sir.

208
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,040
I have my eye on him at all times.

209
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:11,520
As for the shooting instructor,
I’ve found you one.

210
00:11:13,680 --> 00:11:14,680
Shooting?

211
00:11:15,520 --> 00:11:16,160
Yes.

212
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:18,120
Your schedule is currently full,
though, Mr. Pai.

213
00:11:18,640 --> 00:11:20,160
What about Saturday morning?

214
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:24,800
Aren’t you and Mr. Tim going to a district
office for your marriage registration?

215
00:11:28,560 --> 00:11:29,160
That’s right.

216
00:11:30,480 --> 00:11:31,400
I’m sorry.

217
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:35,160
I’m so preoccupied with this matter
with North that I forgot.

218
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:36,880
It’s okay.

219
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:38,160
I understand.

220
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:39,080
We’re not in a rush anyway.

221
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:40,880
Well, cancel that, then.

222
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,600
I want to learn how to use a gun
as soon as possible.

223
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:44,320
Of course, sir.

224
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:09,880
All of these were given as gratuitous gifts,

225
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:11,920
as evidential on our Instagram posts.

226
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:13,200
I’m good to go.

227
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:19,000
He’s learning how to use a gun
just because his cousin gets scammed.

228
00:12:19,240 --> 00:12:21,600
If he finds out he’s in the same boat,
I’m gonna be dead on the spot.

229
00:12:24,880 --> 00:12:25,680
Can this get any worse?

230
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:30,520
Hello, Mr. Prasit.

231
00:12:34,520 --> 00:12:35,160
You look amazing.

232
00:12:38,040 --> 00:12:38,880
Hello, sir.

233
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:40,520
It’s been a while, Tim.

234
00:12:41,880 --> 00:12:44,800
Oh, I’ve just been busy.

235
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:47,280
You gotta make time to pay back
what you owe me, kid.

236
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:49,600
I’m sorry.

237
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:51,120
Everything okay with you?

238
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:55,840
I’m kinda in a pinch lately

239
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:59,600
and I thought maybe you can give me
just a little more time.

240
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:01,960
Of course. Time, I can give you.

241
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:04,400
I don’t recommend you
disappearing on me, though.

242
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:07,240
You’ve been doing so well
at clearing your debt.

243
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:08,560
Right.

244
00:13:09,920 --> 00:13:11,360
I’m definitely not going anywhere—

245
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:14,000
I’m just tying my shoe laces, sir.

246
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:15,160
Don’t worry.

247
00:13:16,120 --> 00:13:17,360
Not a thing to worry about, sir.

248
00:13:17,520 --> 00:13:20,040
My plan is coming along nicely.

249
00:13:20,480 --> 00:13:22,920
All I ask is that you are
a little patient with me, sir.

250
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:23,920
Thank you.

251
00:13:29,560 --> 00:13:30,800
I thought we’re done talking?

252
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:32,080
Can I go?

253
00:13:32,680 --> 00:13:33,120
Please.

254
00:13:33,360 --> 00:13:33,920
Right.

255
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:37,400
I’m really sorry, sir.

256
00:13:37,680 --> 00:13:38,200
Bye.

257
00:13:49,160 --> 00:13:49,960
Pai.

258
00:13:57,600 --> 00:13:58,920
Oh, that…

259
00:13:59,040 --> 00:14:00,880
I didn’t know
people still send hard copy invitations.

260
00:14:03,680 --> 00:14:05,360
Exactly what I was thinking.

261
00:14:05,360 --> 00:14:07,080
Who even does that anymore?

262
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:08,560
Where were you today?

263
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:09,800
Why is your bag so bulky?

264
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:13,000
Oh, I went to the gym.

265
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:16,280
How come you’re home early today?

266
00:14:16,920 --> 00:14:18,800
Nana found me a lawyer.

267
00:14:19,280 --> 00:14:20,840
I hurried home to deal with this matter.

268
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:24,320
Good job, Nana. Good job.

269
00:14:24,760 --> 00:14:27,520
I’m gonna go unpack in the bedroom.

270
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:28,680
Stay here, Pai.

271
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:29,880
I’ll go with you.

272
00:14:43,640 --> 00:14:44,800
You seem tense, baby.

273
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:46,200
Is everything alright?

274
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:48,240
Oh…

275
00:14:48,960 --> 00:14:50,720
You can be honest with me, Tim.

276
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:53,160
Are you…

277
00:15:00,320 --> 00:15:01,280
Mad at me?

278
00:15:02,360 --> 00:15:02,880
What?

279
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:06,360
You were chopping your words and then
barging in here to get away from me.

280
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:07,720
Something just feels wrong.

281
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:09,200
What are you mad at me about?

282
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:10,480
Oh.

283
00:15:13,920 --> 00:15:14,760
It’s…

284
00:15:15,480 --> 00:15:18,960
You’ve been very busy and tense lately.

285
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:21,920
We barely had any alone time at all.

286
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:26,000
You’re right.

287
00:15:27,520 --> 00:15:28,960
I’m sorry.

288
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:32,040
Can you forgive me?

289
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:01,440
We have 40 minutes until the appointment.

290
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:03,000
Alright.

291
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:05,560
What am I, a dog?

292
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:08,000
Thanks.

293
00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:17,640
Yes, Pai?

294
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:19,000
Everything’s okay.

295
00:17:19,280 --> 00:17:20,560
U is still here.

296
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:21,600
Look.

297
00:17:22,640 --> 00:17:23,200
Good.

298
00:17:23,880 --> 00:17:26,480
See me at the meeting room
in the common area in 10 minutes.

299
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:28,040
I got us a lawyer.

300
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:29,640
Yes, Pai.

301
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:39,800
Baby?

302
00:17:42,840 --> 00:17:44,200
Pai got us a lawyer.

303
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:45,480
You’re dead meat, U.

304
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:00,200
Hello.

305
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:01,560
My name is Prem.

306
00:18:01,640 --> 00:18:02,840
I’m U’s lawyer.

307
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:07,920
TWO HOURS PRIOR

308
00:18:13,120 --> 00:18:14,680
YOU KNOW WHO IS BAD
(Here’s the contact of the lawyer I know.)

309
00:18:16,440 --> 00:18:17,800
(I told him about you.)

310
00:18:18,040 --> 00:18:18,920
(He’s going to take the job.)

311
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:20,600
(Delete this chat after you read it.)

312
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:44,200
Let’s begin.

313
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:46,240
Pai, there’s this guy—

314
00:18:46,360 --> 00:18:47,480
North, don’t interrupt.

315
00:18:48,400 --> 00:18:50,000
From what I was told,

316
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:53,000
I think we can sue him for fraud.

317
00:18:53,840 --> 00:18:56,360
Does that mean we can
take legal actions right away?

318
00:18:56,360 --> 00:18:56,440
Does that mean we can
take legal actions right away?

319
00:18:56,520 --> 00:18:56,640
Yes.

320
00:18:57,240 --> 00:18:58,800
However, this will likely become a scandal.

321
00:18:59,840 --> 00:19:04,000
Once we gather enough evidence,
please proceed right away.

322
00:19:04,320 --> 00:19:06,760
Between fame and revenge,

323
00:19:07,760 --> 00:19:08,600
I prefer the latter.

324
00:19:11,520 --> 00:19:13,120
Allow me a question, sir.

325
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:16,160
You want to sue him for fraud.

326
00:19:16,800 --> 00:19:17,840
On what ground are you accusing him?

327
00:19:20,560 --> 00:19:21,480
My name is Prem.

328
00:19:21,680 --> 00:19:22,840
I am Mr. U’s lawyer.

329
00:19:22,840 --> 00:19:25,120
That’s what I was trying to tell you, Pai.

330
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:28,840
He’s a con artist who coaxed
my cousin into marrying him.

331
00:19:29,560 --> 00:19:30,800
That should be enough to put him in jail.

332
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:32,080
If it is that easy,

333
00:19:32,640 --> 00:19:34,720
there would be no need
for four years of law school.

334
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:35,000
Hey.

335
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:38,480
Your cousin was the one who proposed.

336
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:41,800
My client explicitly told him that he did not come from a wealthy background,

337
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:44,400
to which your cousin said he did not mind.

338
00:19:45,440 --> 00:19:49,320
Which means that my client had no intention of deception from the beginning.

339
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:52,560
I think renting a fake house
was pretty intentional.

340
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:54,120
But that is not fraud.

341
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:56,520
My client did not demand
anything from doing so,

342
00:19:57,320 --> 00:20:00,920
except the peace of mind of his husband
and his husband’s family.

343
00:20:01,040 --> 00:20:02,000
It is a fraud.

344
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:03,920
Because he knew that if he impressed me,

345
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:05,640
he would be one step closer to
claiming Empire’s money.

346
00:20:05,880 --> 00:20:08,640
Is there any evidence of
Mr. U’s intention in that regard?

347
00:20:09,320 --> 00:20:10,840
I’m not sure.

348
00:20:11,080 --> 00:20:12,360
But I don’t think there is…

349
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:13,000
Mr. North.

350
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:14,520
Please refrain from answering.

351
00:20:17,280 --> 00:20:17,800
Wait.

352
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:20,520
U took 250 million from me.

353
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:21,880
That’s evidence.

354
00:20:22,160 --> 00:20:22,800
- What?
- What!

355
00:20:25,480 --> 00:20:26,120
What did you say?

356
00:20:27,160 --> 00:20:29,160
I wrote him a check.

357
00:20:31,680 --> 00:20:32,400
Mr. North.

358
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:37,760
Did my client specifically ask you
to give him 250 million?

359
00:20:39,680 --> 00:20:40,800
Mr. North, do not say anything.

360
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:41,200
Right.

361
00:20:41,640 --> 00:20:43,320
Mr. North, do not say anything.

362
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:45,600
I will explain in his place.

363
00:20:46,880 --> 00:20:49,920
When he was proposed to,
my client turned Mr. North down.

364
00:20:50,160 --> 00:20:52,680
His reason was that
their social statuses were too different.

365
00:20:52,920 --> 00:20:57,720
Your cousin, then, offered this 250 million
by way of leveling their statuses

366
00:20:58,440 --> 00:20:59,640
in order to convince U to marry him.

367
00:20:59,760 --> 00:21:00,520
North!

368
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:05,760
Can we stop?

369
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:08,520
I can’t listen to this anymore.

370
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:10,240
Of course we can.

371
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:12,440
This is a waste of time, anyway.

372
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:15,480
If you agree to settle,

373
00:21:16,440 --> 00:21:17,440
we’ll immediately drop this matter.

374
00:21:17,440 --> 00:21:17,960
No!

375
00:21:19,080 --> 00:21:20,600
I insist on pressing charges.

376
00:21:20,840 --> 00:21:23,760
My client finally agreed
to enter into this civil contract.

377
00:21:24,120 --> 00:21:27,320
He has lived with his husband ever since
with no sign of running away.

378
00:21:27,840 --> 00:21:30,440
Would you say that is a fraudulent action?

379
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:33,240
If we can’t sue him for fraud,

380
00:21:34,160 --> 00:21:35,400
we’ll sue him for divorce.

381
00:21:51,320 --> 00:21:54,080
Are we… done talking?

382
00:21:54,280 --> 00:21:55,000
Done talking?

383
00:21:55,360 --> 00:21:56,160
We haven’t even started.

384
00:21:57,920 --> 00:22:00,360
I think it was the right decision
to fall back for a consultation, Mr. Pai.

385
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:01,520
That attorney—

386
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:03,200
I freaking hate his guts!

387
00:22:04,480 --> 00:22:07,520
U dared pull this stunt because
he had connections with such a lawyer.

388
00:22:07,560 --> 00:22:10,360
Anyone who’s friends with that lawyer
must be a dirtbag!

389
00:22:12,720 --> 00:22:13,240
Excuse me.

390
00:22:13,720 --> 00:22:14,560
That went down the wrong pipe.

391
00:22:14,840 --> 00:22:15,560
Please go on.

392
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:16,920
Dirtbag, alright.

393
00:22:17,960 --> 00:22:18,960
As for suing for divorce,

394
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:24,520
the legal grounds for that include adultery, insanity, misconduct, incurable disease,

395
00:22:24,520 --> 00:22:27,880
or physical disability that prevents the couple from fulfilling married life.

396
00:22:28,080 --> 00:22:28,880
Misconduct!

397
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:30,160
He definitely has done that.

398
00:22:30,240 --> 00:22:32,880
In that case, his misconduct must
already have an effect on Mr. North.

399
00:22:33,480 --> 00:22:36,920
Are you saying there has to be a scandal that causes our family financial loss

400
00:22:37,360 --> 00:22:39,680
or defamation before we can sue him?

401
00:22:39,680 --> 00:22:40,080
Yes.

402
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:44,760
The easier way out would be to both agree
to file for an uncontested divorce.

403
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:48,560
However, reclaiming back
the 250 million would be—

404
00:22:48,560 --> 00:22:49,080
Ugh!

405
00:22:49,640 --> 00:22:51,440
Just let him have it!

406
00:22:51,600 --> 00:22:52,160
No.

407
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:56,880
Letting him fool us and walk away free
with 250 million in his pocket?

408
00:22:57,040 --> 00:22:57,840
Only in his dreams.

409
00:22:57,840 --> 00:22:59,400
What do you want me to do?

410
00:22:59,520 --> 00:23:01,760
There’s nothing we can sue him for.

411
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:02,760
Mr. Juean.

412
00:23:03,160 --> 00:23:05,000
What does my cousin have to do
to get his money back?

413
00:23:05,120 --> 00:23:07,240
Negotiate with the other party
to agree to an uncontested divorce,

414
00:23:07,240 --> 00:23:11,320
and have him write a contract to return
the money after the proceedings.

415
00:23:11,440 --> 00:23:14,520
But… I don’t think they will agree.

416
00:23:15,080 --> 00:23:15,360
North.

417
00:23:16,360 --> 00:23:17,200
We need to talk.

418
00:23:18,520 --> 00:23:19,480
All of you can go home.

419
00:23:19,480 --> 00:23:20,240
That’s it for today.

420
00:23:26,920 --> 00:23:27,720
North!

421
00:23:27,720 --> 00:23:28,960
I’m coming!

422
00:23:37,080 --> 00:23:40,840
Let’s go talk somewhere else.

423
00:23:42,640 --> 00:23:45,160
Did the housekeeper
forget to come in today?

424
00:23:45,560 --> 00:23:46,360
Come on.

425
00:23:47,480 --> 00:23:48,960
Your bed is a mess. Oh, sh—

426
00:23:49,800 --> 00:23:52,920
Pai, you’re not allowed
to scold me anymore.

427
00:23:53,160 --> 00:23:54,880
I can’t take anything else today.

428
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:57,160
If you scold me, even one word,

429
00:23:59,160 --> 00:24:00,600
I’m going to run off and become a monk!

430
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:04,480
North, a monk has to
wake up at 4 in the morning,

431
00:24:04,480 --> 00:24:07,040
live without air-conditioning units,
and eat only until lunch.

432
00:24:07,040 --> 00:24:09,480
You can’t even stick to
an intermittent fasting program.

433
00:24:09,480 --> 00:24:11,480
If he wants to play this game,

434
00:24:11,480 --> 00:24:12,480
we’ll play, too.

435
00:24:13,320 --> 00:24:14,320
And we’ll win.

436
00:24:15,560 --> 00:24:16,360
Game?

437
00:24:18,080 --> 00:24:19,040
What do you mean?

438
00:24:22,560 --> 00:24:27,240
Convince him to get a divorce
and give you back everything.

439
00:24:28,920 --> 00:24:30,560
I must ask you to do three things.

440
00:24:30,560 --> 00:24:32,520
Do not believe a word
that comes out of his mouth.

441
00:24:32,880 --> 00:24:33,680
Second,

442
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:35,840
do not let anyone
know about this.

443
00:24:36,400 --> 00:24:37,200
Third…

444
00:24:39,480 --> 00:24:41,240
Do not fall in love with him again.

445
00:24:45,880 --> 00:24:48,280
I can do that… probably.

446
00:24:48,280 --> 00:24:50,920
We won’t let him have anything.

447
00:24:56,920 --> 00:24:58,760
I’m sorry, Pai.

448
00:24:59,840 --> 00:25:03,040
I didn’t think a sheet of paper
like a marriage certificate

449
00:25:03,360 --> 00:25:05,280
would be such a big deal.

450
00:25:45,960 --> 00:25:47,640
WHAT TO KNOW
BEFORE YOU SAY “I DO”

451
00:25:47,640 --> 00:25:48,560
MARITAL PROPERTY

452
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:51,120
PROPERTY ACQUIRED DURING A MARRIAGE IS SHARED EQUALLY BETWEEN PARTNERS.

453
00:25:53,720 --> 00:25:56,280
YOUR OWN KIND OF DIVORCE

454
00:26:25,680 --> 00:26:27,000
Hello, Nana.

455
00:26:41,440 --> 00:26:43,320
You didn’t sleep well?

456
00:26:43,320 --> 00:26:45,360
You seem tired.

457
00:26:47,800 --> 00:26:48,960
Baby.

458
00:26:49,280 --> 00:26:51,080
Is there anything you want right now?

459
00:26:52,480 --> 00:26:56,160
Something like watches, cars, or a condo.

460
00:26:58,320 --> 00:26:59,720
What would I need them for?

461
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:01,440
I already have them.

462
00:27:02,600 --> 00:27:03,960
Why are you asking?

463
00:27:05,600 --> 00:27:08,440
Are you trying to make up
for something you did?

464
00:27:14,840 --> 00:27:15,960
Come on.

465
00:27:16,840 --> 00:27:17,960
Talk to me.

466
00:27:18,520 --> 00:27:19,320
What happened?

467
00:27:19,520 --> 00:27:20,120
I…

468
00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:23,480
I don’t want to get married anymore.

469
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:36,960
If we’re legally married,
it’ll be harder to manage our assets.

470
00:27:36,960 --> 00:27:40,360
And it will be even harder for me
since my assets are tied to Empire’s.

471
00:27:45,160 --> 00:27:47,400
You’re worried because of what happened
with U and North, aren’t you?

472
00:27:47,400 --> 00:27:49,280
It’s not that I don’t trust you, baby.

473
00:27:49,760 --> 00:27:52,560
I just need time to sort out my assets first.

474
00:27:57,720 --> 00:27:59,480
So that was it.

475
00:27:59,480 --> 00:28:01,120
You scared me for a second.

476
00:28:01,480 --> 00:28:03,400
I thought you were breaking up with me.

477
00:28:03,400 --> 00:28:05,200
You’re not mad at me?

478
00:28:05,880 --> 00:28:06,720
I’m not.

479
00:28:07,320 --> 00:28:09,200
When do I ever disagree with you?

480
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:10,880
I’m alright as long as we’re together.

481
00:28:10,880 --> 00:28:11,680
eally?

482
00:28:13,080 --> 00:28:14,440
Come on here.

483
00:28:14,440 --> 00:28:15,680
Look at your face.

484
00:28:31,560 --> 00:28:34,560
If you’re going to stay here,
this is how we live.

485
00:28:35,240 --> 00:28:37,160
If you can’t live like this,
then go ahead and divorce me.

486
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:41,320
I’m more than ready.

487
00:28:43,200 --> 00:28:46,480
I’m staying because
there is no need for me to run away.

488
00:28:46,640 --> 00:28:50,520
You’re not running away because
you don’t want to be sued for fraud.

489
00:28:50,920 --> 00:28:51,720
No.

490
00:28:52,160 --> 00:28:53,000
It’s because I love you.

491
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:53,960
I don’t believe you!

492
00:28:53,960 --> 00:28:57,280
If you stay, I’ll make sure every day
is a living hell for you.

493
00:28:57,320 --> 00:28:59,840
You’ll beg for divorce and for your life!

494
00:29:02,040 --> 00:29:02,840
I’m so scared.

495
00:29:02,840 --> 00:29:04,400
I get chills down my spine.

496
00:29:06,960 --> 00:29:08,200
I’m gonna cry.

497
00:29:13,120 --> 00:29:15,600
Scared, are you?

498
00:29:15,600 --> 00:29:17,440
You’re so great, huh?

499
00:29:23,080 --> 00:29:24,160
Thanks, North.

500
00:29:24,160 --> 00:29:26,440
You threw me these pillows because
you’re worried about me,

501
00:29:27,120 --> 00:29:28,160
aren’t you?

502
00:29:28,160 --> 00:29:29,480
Worried? As if!

503
00:29:30,920 --> 00:29:32,880
Someone’s in denial.

504
00:29:40,600 --> 00:29:41,400
North.

505
00:29:41,680 --> 00:29:42,440
North.

506
00:29:42,440 --> 00:29:43,480
I need to pee.

507
00:30:00,640 --> 00:30:05,880
♪ Why must it be me who hurts ♪

508
00:30:05,880 --> 00:30:08,200
♪ For loving you ♪

509
00:30:08,200 --> 00:30:09,480
Stop right there!

510
00:30:09,480 --> 00:30:10,560
What do you think you’re doing?

511
00:30:10,560 --> 00:30:11,640
Get back in there.

512
00:30:13,280 --> 00:30:15,720
♪ Why must it be me ♪

513
00:30:15,720 --> 00:30:18,320
♪ It’s a lie ♪

514
00:30:18,320 --> 00:30:21,640
♪ Why do I feel like I’m about to die ♪

515
00:30:21,640 --> 00:30:25,040
♪ For loving you ♪

516
00:30:25,040 --> 00:30:27,040
♪ …who cries ♪

517
00:30:27,040 --> 00:30:30,400
♪ I heard love’s good for the heart ♪

518
00:30:30,400 --> 00:30:33,840
♪ For loving you ♪

519
00:31:25,240 --> 00:31:26,280
What are you doing?

520
00:31:26,560 --> 00:31:28,520
It’s me who has to ask you that.

521
00:31:28,920 --> 00:31:29,920
I’m not doing anything.

522
00:31:32,920 --> 00:31:36,120
“Playing with a dog
will get your lips licked.”

523
00:31:36,120 --> 00:31:37,320
You heard of that?

524
00:31:48,160 --> 00:31:49,280
Who’s playing with you?

525
00:31:49,920 --> 00:31:50,760
Not me.

526
00:31:54,760 --> 00:31:55,560
North.

527
00:31:56,280 --> 00:31:57,880
Stop. Stop right there.

528
00:32:01,360 --> 00:32:02,160
Stop.

529
00:32:13,040 --> 00:32:14,280
Okay.

530
00:32:14,280 --> 00:32:17,360
Stop it, North. Stop.

531
00:32:17,640 --> 00:32:18,640
Don’t be swayed.

532
00:32:19,040 --> 00:32:20,320
Don’t cave in.

533
00:32:25,280 --> 00:32:26,080
Hey!

534
00:32:26,520 --> 00:32:27,520
I told you to stop!

535
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:20,600
How did you get out of there?

536
00:33:20,600 --> 00:33:21,960
I sneaked out.

537
00:33:21,960 --> 00:33:24,120
I have to be back soon
before North finds out.

538
00:33:24,440 --> 00:33:26,280
You’re freaking annoying, you know that?

539
00:33:26,760 --> 00:33:29,800
You got everything you wanted
and got away with it.

540
00:33:29,800 --> 00:33:33,480
Meanwhile, I did everything right and my
plan still went sideways because of you!

541
00:33:33,480 --> 00:33:34,280
Hey.

542
00:33:34,280 --> 00:33:36,200
Your target is as vicious as a dog.

543
00:33:36,200 --> 00:33:38,160
You can’t blame me for that!

544
00:33:38,720 --> 00:33:41,800
If he and I don’t get married legally,

545
00:33:42,080 --> 00:33:44,960
I will have done all this for nothing.

546
00:33:46,200 --> 00:33:51,040
Then you have to do whatever it takes for
Mr. Pai to sign that marriage certificate.

547
00:33:51,040 --> 00:33:53,480
And how do I do that?
Enlighten me, Mr. Amazing.

548
00:33:54,520 --> 00:33:59,120
There are actually a few reasons
why people get legally married.

549
00:33:59,120 --> 00:34:03,800
There are certain rights only
the spouse or family can exercise.

550
00:34:12,240 --> 00:34:16,200
We still see a decrease in tourist number
within this trimester.

551
00:34:16,600 --> 00:34:21,600
We have come up with campaigns and
had collaborations with different banks

552
00:34:21,600 --> 00:34:23,680
to ensure more credit card privileges.

553
00:34:23,680 --> 00:34:24,600
Ugh.

554
00:34:24,600 --> 00:34:26,640
Your phone keeps ringing,
did someone die?

555
00:34:29,280 --> 00:34:30,080
Excuse me.

556
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:34,200
(Hello.)

557
00:34:34,200 --> 00:34:36,280
(Are you
Mr. Thanin Chaiyanuwat’s family?)

558
00:34:36,600 --> 00:34:37,560
Yes.

559
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:39,160
Did something happen?

560
00:34:39,160 --> 00:34:41,560
(Mr. Thanin was in a car accident.)

561
00:34:42,080 --> 00:34:45,000
What?
What did you just say?

562
00:34:50,920 --> 00:34:52,000
Please, be careful.

563
00:34:59,880 --> 00:35:00,680
Baby.

564
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:03,800
Pai.

565
00:35:07,960 --> 00:35:09,240
I’m sorry.

566
00:35:09,240 --> 00:35:10,200
Are you in pain?

567
00:35:10,400 --> 00:35:11,320
What did the doctor say?

568
00:35:11,320 --> 00:35:12,560
Is it serious?

569
00:35:13,880 --> 00:35:15,640
You ask more questions than the doctor.

570
00:35:16,920 --> 00:35:18,680
What exactly happened?

571
00:35:21,920 --> 00:35:23,680
TWO HOURS PRIOR

572
00:35:26,040 --> 00:35:28,520
(The main reason
people get legally married)

573
00:35:28,520 --> 00:35:30,920
(is the right to decide
during medical emergencies.)

574
00:35:31,040 --> 00:35:32,800
Medical emergencies…

575
00:35:32,800 --> 00:35:34,320
How hard can it be?

576
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:37,960
Crashing at 30 km/h
will only dent the bumper.

577
00:35:38,800 --> 00:35:41,760
For it to be an emergency, I gotta go at 60!

578
00:35:42,960 --> 00:35:45,360
Come on!

579
00:35:51,360 --> 00:35:52,960
Who the hell would do that!

580
00:35:54,160 --> 00:35:55,040
Oh, shit!

581
00:35:59,280 --> 00:36:05,680
Someone bumped into the back of my car
and I swerved off the road into a tree.

582
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:08,760
But the doctor said it’s nothing serious.

583
00:36:14,120 --> 00:36:16,440
I thought I’d never see you again.

584
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:18,360
Don’t say that.

585
00:36:21,160 --> 00:36:22,640
Are you in pain?

586
00:36:24,760 --> 00:36:27,640
I’d love to act cool and tell you I’m not,

587
00:36:27,920 --> 00:36:28,720
but…

588
00:36:29,800 --> 00:36:30,600
It hurts.

589
00:36:32,040 --> 00:36:33,760
Pai, be gentle!

590
00:37:24,880 --> 00:37:27,440
Don’t you have to go back to work?

591
00:37:27,440 --> 00:37:29,000
I’m troubling you, aren’t I?

592
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:30,760
You were in a car crash.

593
00:37:31,040 --> 00:37:32,800
I don’t care about anything else.

594
00:37:38,320 --> 00:37:41,000
It feels nice to have someone
take care of me when I’m not alright.

595
00:37:47,040 --> 00:37:48,200
You know…

596
00:37:49,760 --> 00:37:51,840
I’ve never been more scared of anything.

597
00:37:52,960 --> 00:37:57,080
When I was on my way to the hospital,
I couldn’t even cry.

598
00:38:06,320 --> 00:38:09,320
It was reasonably scary.

599
00:38:22,480 --> 00:38:25,000
You’re my whole world, Tim.

600
00:38:25,440 --> 00:38:28,640
I don’t know how I’d live without you.

601
00:38:34,360 --> 00:38:36,200
I’m so glad I’m still alive.

602
00:38:48,560 --> 00:38:52,600
When you’re all recovered,
let’s get married at the district office.

603
00:38:54,200 --> 00:38:55,480
You changed your mind?

604
00:38:58,360 --> 00:39:00,800
We’ve planned to do
a lot of things together,

605
00:39:01,400 --> 00:39:03,040
let’s start now.

606
00:39:19,520 --> 00:39:21,920
How do I win a divorce case?

607
00:39:21,920 --> 00:39:25,640
Popular legal grounds for divorce sustained by court include:

608
00:39:25,640 --> 00:39:28,440
sexual affair from either party or bigamy,

609
00:39:28,440 --> 00:39:31,400
in which case usually successfullyresult in divorce given enough evidence,

610
00:39:31,400 --> 00:39:36,200
such as chats, photos, videos, cohabitation, or children.

611
00:39:36,200 --> 00:39:37,120
Too difficult.

612
00:39:37,120 --> 00:39:38,880
Give me something easier.

613
00:39:38,880 --> 00:39:41,520
Come on in. Come on in.

614
00:39:45,080 --> 00:39:46,600
What are you doing?

615
00:39:46,600 --> 00:39:47,680
Why are you looking into that?

616
00:39:47,680 --> 00:39:49,600
I want to divorce U.

617
00:39:49,600 --> 00:39:50,200
What?

618
00:39:50,600 --> 00:39:51,200
Divorce?

619
00:39:52,440 --> 00:39:54,000
When did you even get married?

620
00:39:55,560 --> 00:39:56,720
It’s a long story.

621
00:39:56,720 --> 00:39:58,280
I’ll tell you later.

622
00:39:58,920 --> 00:40:01,680
But right now, I want a divorce!

623
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:08,040
You want a divorce.
Was it like, you were drunk,

624
00:40:08,040 --> 00:40:11,880
and got married in Las Vegas?

625
00:40:13,480 --> 00:40:14,800
Was it like that?

626
00:40:15,320 --> 00:40:16,360
Something like that.

627
00:40:16,680 --> 00:40:19,000
But he refuses to get a divorce.

628
00:40:23,560 --> 00:40:25,760
Or… You can use me.

629
00:40:26,400 --> 00:40:27,200
What?

630
00:40:45,400 --> 00:40:46,360
Oh.

631
00:40:47,200 --> 00:40:48,160
Are you here to see North?

632
00:40:48,160 --> 00:40:48,960
Yes.

633
00:40:48,960 --> 00:40:50,880
Can I wait inside?

634
00:40:50,880 --> 00:40:53,400
North will probably be home late.

635
00:40:54,240 --> 00:40:55,040
Of course.

636
00:41:06,640 --> 00:41:07,760
(He told me…)

637
00:41:08,240 --> 00:41:09,760
(I need to make you like me.)

638
00:41:10,000 --> 00:41:11,080
(When did you do that?)

639
00:41:11,400 --> 00:41:12,400
(I didn’t see it.)

640
00:41:12,560 --> 00:41:13,840
(How can I find time to do it?)

641
00:41:13,840 --> 00:41:16,560
(Use me to fake an affair.)

642
00:41:16,560 --> 00:41:19,360
You can use this as evidence to sue him.

643
00:41:25,680 --> 00:41:27,600
Oh, this is so scary!

644
00:41:27,920 --> 00:41:29,000
What is?

645
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:30,400
We’re not watching a horror film.

646
00:41:31,120 --> 00:41:32,960
I’m scared of the dark.

647
00:41:33,520 --> 00:41:34,440
The dark?

648
00:41:35,360 --> 00:41:37,560
Should we change the channel?

649
00:41:37,560 --> 00:41:39,280
Something like a seahorse documentary?

650
00:41:39,280 --> 00:41:40,640
What do you think?

651
00:41:41,080 --> 00:41:42,360
Let’s watch this.

652
00:41:42,360 --> 00:41:43,640
It’s fun.

653
00:41:46,160 --> 00:41:47,440
Hey!

654
00:41:47,440 --> 00:41:48,600
What the hell are you doing?

655
00:41:48,600 --> 00:41:49,480
I’m your best friend’s boyfriend!

656
00:41:49,480 --> 00:41:50,640
Don’t you care about North at all?

657
00:41:50,800 --> 00:41:51,960
Shhh.

658
00:41:52,800 --> 00:41:56,680
If we both stay quiet,
nobody has to get hurt.

659
00:41:58,560 --> 00:41:59,720
Get away from me!

660
00:42:01,720 --> 00:42:02,960
I’m faithful to North.

661
00:42:03,440 --> 00:42:04,320
He’s the only man I love.

662
00:42:17,840 --> 00:42:19,680
Don’t worry about North.

663
00:42:20,080 --> 00:42:21,920
He handed you down to me.

664
00:42:23,360 --> 00:42:25,040
North won’t be mad at you.

665
00:42:29,000 --> 00:42:29,680
Stop!

666
00:42:29,680 --> 00:42:30,920
That’s enough, Pure.

667
00:42:32,400 --> 00:42:34,560
Why are you interrupting me?

668
00:42:34,960 --> 00:42:36,640
We almost got it!

669
00:42:36,640 --> 00:42:38,520
Why did you have to stop me?

670
00:42:42,440 --> 00:42:43,720
North, North.

671
00:42:43,720 --> 00:42:45,520
Get a grip, dude.

672
00:42:45,520 --> 00:42:46,520
You’re hurting me.

673
00:42:48,280 --> 00:42:49,280
Crap.

674
00:42:50,040 --> 00:42:51,040
I’m sorry.

675
00:42:52,960 --> 00:42:55,280
Are you upset because you still love him?

676
00:42:56,080 --> 00:42:56,880
No.

677
00:42:58,200 --> 00:43:02,280
Why don’t you work things out with
the Inside Out in your head first?

678
00:43:02,280 --> 00:43:04,200
Do you even want to get a divorce?

679
00:43:04,680 --> 00:43:05,720
Of course, I do.

680
00:43:07,000 --> 00:43:07,800
North.

681
00:43:08,240 --> 00:43:11,600
You’re not someone who
ignores his own emotions.

682
00:43:13,680 --> 00:43:15,240
This is probably the first time.

683
00:43:16,040 --> 00:43:18,120
It’s only normal that
you find it difficult to do.

684
00:43:20,320 --> 00:43:23,080
I want a divorce, but he doesn’t.

685
00:43:23,080 --> 00:43:24,320
He wants my money.

686
00:43:25,560 --> 00:43:26,560
Really?

687
00:43:27,400 --> 00:43:35,680
But the look on his face when I told him you gave him away was really sad.

688
00:43:35,680 --> 00:43:37,800
He handed you down to me.

689
00:43:38,520 --> 00:43:39,080
What?

690
00:43:39,960 --> 00:43:41,040
What did you say?

691
00:43:41,640 --> 00:43:43,080
North and I always do this

692
00:43:43,080 --> 00:43:46,680
when it comes to something
we think is disposable.

693
00:43:48,280 --> 00:43:50,120
You don’t have to worry.

694
00:43:50,400 --> 00:43:52,120
North won’t be mad at you.

695
00:44:06,640 --> 00:44:07,640
What were you trying to do?

696
00:44:07,640 --> 00:44:08,680
That’s my business.

697
00:44:08,680 --> 00:44:10,960
It is your business,
but it almost became mine.

698
00:44:10,960 --> 00:44:12,840
If you were just a little bit too late,

699
00:44:12,840 --> 00:44:13,680
I would have—

700
00:44:13,680 --> 00:44:14,440
What?

701
00:44:14,960 --> 00:44:16,600
If I was too late,

702
00:44:16,840 --> 00:44:18,120
what would have happened?

703
00:44:21,720 --> 00:44:23,720
What would have happened, I wonder,

704
00:44:23,720 --> 00:44:25,800
if you didn’t come in…

705
00:44:26,720 --> 00:44:27,720
North!

706
00:44:29,360 --> 00:44:30,480
Are you really mad at me?

707
00:44:30,920 --> 00:44:31,800
What the hell?

708
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:33,520
This was his idea.

709
00:44:33,520 --> 00:44:34,160
North!

710
00:44:43,800 --> 00:44:45,200
So here you are.

711
00:44:47,040 --> 00:44:48,080
Stop.

712
00:44:48,080 --> 00:44:49,120
Don’t go.

713
00:44:49,960 --> 00:44:52,200
I’m the one who should be mad at you.

714
00:44:52,200 --> 00:44:53,240
I’m not mad.

715
00:44:53,800 --> 00:44:55,360
I want a divorce.

716
00:44:56,120 --> 00:44:56,920
North.

717
00:44:57,480 --> 00:44:58,840
Why are you doing this?

718
00:45:00,120 --> 00:45:02,200
Did you really give me away?

719
00:45:02,200 --> 00:45:03,920
Or were you just trying to fake evidence?

720
00:45:03,920 --> 00:45:05,520
Which case do you want it to be?

721
00:45:08,240 --> 00:45:10,440
The latter.

722
00:45:11,000 --> 00:45:13,280
The former would break my heart.

723
00:45:18,560 --> 00:45:20,880
Will you just stop lying to me?

724
00:45:21,480 --> 00:45:23,520
I stopped trusting you a long time ago.

725
00:45:26,280 --> 00:45:28,840
I haven’t been lying for a long time now.

726
00:45:29,120 --> 00:45:31,920
You know everything
that happened was real.

727
00:45:34,400 --> 00:45:35,120
North.

728
00:45:35,800 --> 00:45:37,160
Will you please talk to me?

729
00:45:39,200 --> 00:45:41,200
I don’t know what I’m feeling.

730
00:45:41,560 --> 00:45:43,040
My head is a mess.

731
00:45:44,560 --> 00:45:48,520
I don’t even know if I still love you.

732
00:45:57,320 --> 00:46:00,160
Well, shall we find out?

733
00:46:48,600 --> 00:46:52,360
The dishes we’ll be serving today
are the samples of the dishes

734
00:46:52,360 --> 00:46:54,200
you chose for the wedding, sirs.

735
00:46:55,120 --> 00:46:55,920
Right.

736
00:46:56,760 --> 00:46:59,440
Allow us some time to consult.

737
00:46:59,880 --> 00:47:02,640
I’ll let you know through Nana
what we think.

738
00:47:02,640 --> 00:47:03,320
Thank you.

739
00:47:03,320 --> 00:47:04,920
This way, please.

740
00:47:16,520 --> 00:47:17,720
Baby.

741
00:47:17,720 --> 00:47:19,240
Is everything okay?

742
00:47:22,320 --> 00:47:25,880
I was butting heads with Aunt Kia
before I came here.

743
00:47:26,720 --> 00:47:27,520
About what?

744
00:47:31,000 --> 00:47:33,080
About leaving work to take care of you.

745
00:47:34,360 --> 00:47:38,760
She called me irresponsible and unable
to separate work from my private life.

746
00:47:39,640 --> 00:47:43,880
She kept saying
I was wasting everyone’s time.

747
00:47:47,480 --> 00:47:50,760
I’m sorry for putting you through that.

748
00:47:53,600 --> 00:47:57,000
When money and profit are at stake,

749
00:47:57,960 --> 00:48:01,400
no one cares that I am
just a human being with feelings.

750
00:48:04,760 --> 00:48:06,760
I don’t want to live like this anymore.

751
00:48:08,640 --> 00:48:10,600
I want to step down
from my role at Empire.

752
00:48:11,960 --> 00:48:12,760
What?

753
00:48:20,600 --> 00:48:22,720
Maybe we can start
a gated community project.

754
00:48:23,040 --> 00:48:24,800
You’re an architect, after all.

755
00:48:24,800 --> 00:48:26,480
Let’s make something of ourselves.

756
00:48:26,680 --> 00:48:27,360
But—

757
00:48:27,360 --> 00:48:28,040
Please?

758
00:48:28,440 --> 00:48:29,880
I can’t keep living like this.

759
00:48:30,640 --> 00:48:31,840
I just want to be with you, Tim.

760
00:48:55,520 --> 00:48:57,000
Listen to me, U.

761
00:48:57,000 --> 00:48:59,080
You gotta do what he wants deep down

762
00:48:59,080 --> 00:49:00,400
without his asking.

763
00:49:01,640 --> 00:49:02,680
I’ll do everything in my power for you

764
00:49:02,680 --> 00:49:03,720
to fall in love with me again.

765
00:49:03,720 --> 00:49:05,680
Where did you get all these ideas?

766
00:49:05,880 --> 00:49:08,120
I just… watch and learn.

767
00:49:08,440 --> 00:49:09,480
Stop it, you!

768
00:49:09,680 --> 00:49:11,040
Do you remember Kuea, baby?

769
00:49:11,080 --> 00:49:12,280
My name is Kuea.

770
00:49:12,280 --> 00:49:13,120
I’m Pai’s friend.

771
00:49:13,120 --> 00:49:14,360
I’m Tim.

772
00:49:14,360 --> 00:49:15,200
His boyfriend.

773
00:49:15,200 --> 00:49:16,200
What’s wrong with you?

774
00:49:16,200 --> 00:49:17,000
Nothing.

775
00:49:17,200 --> 00:49:18,120
Are you jealous?

776
00:49:19,120 --> 00:49:20,880
Let’s start a family.

